=================================================
[Concepts]

Main focus is building simple and intuitive UI with scalable design system.


Business Flow:
	- User open web dashboard
	- User create prompt on input text
	- Once user click "Generate Image" button, the image result will be shown as thumbnail image in the "Gallery", bottom side of page.
	- Each image will have a "Regenerate" button to set the related prompt on the input text, so that user can edit pre-existed prompt to generate new prompt and image.
	- Each image will also have clickable buttons to view full screen and download the image.
	- The images will persist in the gallery even after user refresh the page.


Technical Design:
	- sessionId generated every page open and saved in localStorage of browser, so similar browser will be recognize as the same sessionId until it is removed by clear data.
	- every prompt submitted to backend, will generate promptId, that can be correlated with specific image result, and bound to parent sessionId. So multiple sessions can be held without sharing images between them.
	- sessionId, promptId and imageLink are saved in the DB at backend, so those can be persist over refresh pages.
	- Use preset when querying image from AI API, to improve relevance.



Design Architecture:

In order to achieve scalability, need granular layers of a system. Thus, here are the design:

FE (NextJs - React) - BE (Express - Prisma - SQLite) - Pollinations AI - Cloudinary (Cloud Image Service)



Why choosing those tech stacks:

- NextJs (React) at FE because it support client side and server side. Even though currently only use client side, but later on it still can be expanded into server side for better SEO.

- ExpressJs (nodeJs) at BE because naturally async. Appropriate for API GW which its core function is dispatching requests to core backend systems.

- Prisma is used for an abstraction layer between express and DB, make possibility to use SQLite for MVP, and changeable to PostgreSQL at growth later on.

- SQLite is a small DB for MVP purpose. Once this app grows, recommended to upgrade into more production grade DB like PostgreSQL.

- Pollinations AI is a AI API service which able to generate image. Appropriate for MangGo use case.

- Cloudinary as a cloud-based image storage, is used for scalability purpose.



